  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `1.7.2-1.8.1`\r\nOS & Version: Windows 10 - 512 GB RAM, 3x2TB Samsung Evo 850 pro\r\nCommit hash : (if `develop`)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nGeth to access and use memory without crashing.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nINFO [02-23|04:44:37] Imported new chain segment               blocks=13 txs=1457 mgas=79.030  elapsed=9.504s  mgasps=8.315  number=5139434 hash=40d911…eb0bbf cache=73.91mB\r\nINFO [02-23|04:44:43] Imported new chain segment               blocks=7  txs=846  mgas=55.864  elapsed=6.859s  mgasps=8.144  number=5139441 hash=83bd38…ba8b33 cache=76.89mB\r\nfatal error: out of memory\r\nruntime: out of memory: cannot allocate 131072-byte block (34350235648 in use)\r\nfatal error: out of memory\r\nruntime: out of memory: cannot allocate 131072-byte block (34350235648 in use)\r\nfatal error: out of memory\r\nfatal error: out of memory\r\n\r\nruntime stack:\r\nruntime.throw(0xf32a19, 0xd)\r\n        C:/go/src/runtime/panic.go:605 +0x9c\r\nruntime.largeAlloc(0x1a000, 0xc0675e0100, 0x3)\r\n        C:/go/src/runtime/malloc.go:829 +0x11b\r\nruntime.mallocgc.func1()\r\n        C:/go/src/runtime/malloc.go:722 +0x4d\r\nruntime.systemstack(0xc4cd691538)\r\n        C:/go/src/runtime/asm_amd64.s:344 +0x7e\r\nruntime.mstart()\r\n        C:/go/src/runtime/proc.go:1135\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\nRun geth and wait, or update to 1.8.1\r\n\r\n#### Backtrace\r\n\r\nTo top if off now geth will NOT initiate as I get this exception: \"missing block number for head header hash\"!!\r\n\r\nThis is getting out of hand!\r\n\r\n````\r\n[backtrace]\r\n````\r\n",
