    "body": "I forgot to paste the description:\r\n\r\nFor as long as I can remember the geth on Windows simply crashes, and takes Ethereum wallet GUI with it.\r\n\r\nRunning geth in console mode and then starting the GUI will prevent this and also truly show what is going on.\r\n\r\nAfter the last update to 1.8.1 the crash of geth has gotten absolutely bonkers as it will crash after just a few minutes!\r\n\r\nThis is not a system/hardware issue as I’m running on 512 GB RAM, 3x2TB Samsung Evo 850 pro.\r\n\r\nI have set up geth to use 32gb cache, and clearly see that the crash happens long BEFORE utilizing the 32GB.\r\n\r\nI have tried to roll-back to 1.8.0 which crashed only sporadically, but the 1.8.1 update seems to have corrupted and made the memory corruption absolutely insane.\r\n\r\nThis problem has been going on for years and there are so many articles/reports/tickets on this gone unanswered and without any ownership from development so I wonder why we should bother running a full node anymore as the blockchain is becoming a TB monster fast.\r\n",
