    "created_at": "2018-04-13T18:19:29Z",
    "updated_at": "2018-04-13T18:19:29Z",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Running 1.8.x even with a cache of 2GB set definitely exceeds it when trying to sync up in full-sync mode. We've got some nodes running inside Kubernetes and had limited them to a max of 3GB for each docker container instance. They regularly exceed that even when the cache is set to `2048`.\r\n\r\nWe're running the nodes in proper `fast-sync` mode but once they are all caught up when geth restarts if there is chainstate then I think it will attempt to sync up again in regular full mode. The CPU and Memory used by geth will max out the machine.",
